quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,121,"They said: "
  7,122,""
  7,123,"Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) said: "
  8,55,"Verily, The worst of moving (living) creatures before Allâh are those who disbelieve{1}, - so they shall not believe.",footnotes:1:(V.55) i.e. disbelieve in their Lord (Allâh), deny His Oneness, worship others besides Him, deny His Messengers, and believe not in the Divine Revelation.
  8,56,"They are those with whom you made a covenant, but they break their covenant every time and they do not fear Allâh."
  8,57,"So if you gain the mastery over them in war, punish them severely in order to disperse those who are behind them, so that they may learn a lesson."
  9,25,"Truly Allâh has given you victory on many battle fields, and on the Day of Hunain (battle) when you rejoiced at your great number, but it availed you naught and the earth, vast as it is, was straitened for you, then you turned back in flight."
  9,26,"Then Allâh did send down His Sakînah (calmness, tranquillity and reassurance) on the Messenger (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم), and on the believers, and sent down forces (angels) which you saw not, and punished the disbelievers. Such is the recompense of disbelievers."
  9,27,"Then after that Allâh will accept the repentance of whom He wills. And Allâh is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful."